16 SWINE FARM SITING ACT TECHNICAL CORRECTION
17 SECTION 6.(a) G.S. 106-803(a2) reads as rewritten:
18 "(a2) No component of a liquid animal waste management system for which a permit is
19 required under Part 1 or 1A Part 1A of Article 21 of Chapter 143 of the General Statutes, other
20 than a land application site, shall be constructed on land that is located within the 100-year
21 floodplain."
22 SECTION 6.(b) G.S. 106-805 reads as rewritten:
23 "§ 106-805. Written notice of swine farms.
24 Any person who intends to construct a swine farm whose animal waste management system
25 is subject to a permit under Part 1 or 1A Part 1A of Article 21 of Chapter 143 of the General
26 Statutes shall, after completing a site evaluation and before the farm site is modified, notify all
27 adjoining property owners; all property owners who own property located across a public road,
28 street, or highway from the swine farm; the county or counties in which the farm site is located;
29 and the local health department or departments having jurisdiction over the farm site of that
30 person's intent to construct the swine farm. This notice shall be by certified mail sent to the
31 address on record at the property tax office in the county in which the land is located. Notice to
32 a county shall be sent to the county manager or, if there is no county manager, to the chair of the
33 board of county commissioners. Notice to a local health department shall be sent to the local
34 health director. The written notice shall include all of the following:
35 (1) The name and address of the person intending to construct a swine farm.
36 (2) The type of swine farm and the design capacity of the animal waste
37 management system.
38 (3) The name and address of the technical specialist preparing the waste
39 management plan.
40 (4) The address of the local Soil and Water Conservation District office.
41 (5) Information informing the adjoining property owners and the property owners
42 who own property located across a public road, street, or highway from the
43 swine farm that they may submit written comments to the Division of Water
44 Resources, Department of Environmental Quality."
