16 MODIFY REQUIREMENTS FOR COMPOSTING OF EQUINE AND BOVINE
17 MORTALITY
18 SECTION 9.(a) Definitions. – For purposes of this section, "Disposal Systems Rule"
19 means 15A NCAC 02T .0113 (Permitting By Regulation).
20 SECTION 9.(b) Disposal System Rule. – Until the effective date of the revised
21 permanent rules that the Environmental Management Commission is required to adopt pursuant
22 to subsection (d) of this section, the Commission shall implement the Disposal System Rule as
23 provided in subsection (c) of this section.
24 SECTION 9.(c) Implementation. – Notwithstanding any provision of Subchapter
25 02T of Title 15A of the North Carolina Administrative Code, the Environmental Management
26 Commission shall deem a disposal system to be permitted pursuant to G.S. 143-215.1(b) and not
27 require individual permits or coverage under a general permit provided the system if the disposal
28 system meets all of the following criteria:
29 (1) The disposal system is a composting facility for equine or bovine mortality.
30 (2) The disposal system does not result in any violations of surface water or
31 groundwater standards.
32 (3) The disposal system does not directly discharge to surface waters.
33 (4) The construction and operation of the facilities are approved by the North
34 Carolina Department of Agriculture and Consumer Services.
35 (5) The facilities are approved by the State Veterinarian pursuant to G.S. 106-403.
36 (6) In the event of an imminent threat of a contagious animal disease, any
37 emergency measure or procedure related to composting of animal mortality
38 pursuant to G.S. 106-399.4(a) is authorized.
39 SECTION 9.(d) Additional Rulemaking Authority. – The Commission shall adopt
40 rules to amend the Disposal System Rule consistent with subsection (c) of this section.
41 Notwithstanding G.S. 150B-19(4), the rules adopted by the Commission pursuant to this section
42 shall be substantively identical to the provisions of subsection (c) of this section. Rules adopted
43 pursuant to this section are not subject to Part 3 of Article 2A of Chapter 150B of the General
44 Statutes. Rules adopted pursuant to this section shall become effective as provided in
45 G.S. 150B-21.3(b1), as though 10 or more written objections had been received as provided in
46 G.S. 150B-21.3(b2).
47 SECTION 9.(e) Sunset. – This section expires when permanent rules adopted as
48 required by subsection (d) of this section become effective.
49
