44 signature to the certificate.
45 (2) An electronic signature pad that captures the signature live and then transfers
46 it to the certificate.
47 (c) The weighers of tobacco in leaf tobacco warehouses may use, instead of the seal, their
48 signatures in ink or other indelible substance posted in a conspicuous and accessible place in the
49 warehouse. All seals remain the property of the State and shall be returned to the Commissioner
50 upon termination of duties as a public weighmaster."
